Class PersonBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.databuilder.DataBuilder<T,B>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ValueGenerator<Person>

    public class PersonBuilder
extends PersonBuilderBase<Person,PersonBuilder>
    Builder class for creating a new Person. The simplest usage is 
       new PersonBuilder().createAndCommit()
    which creates a Person with many fields defaulted.

      • PersonBuilder

        public PersonBuilder(int code,
                     boolean withDefaultOfficialID)
        Constructs a PersonBuilder with many fields defaulted. The code parameter (up to 4 digits) is incorporated as a prefix or suffix into many of the generated values. If withDefaultOfficialID is set to true, then an SSN is generated and used in both the OfficialID and TaxID.

        The following defaults are provided:

        FieldValue
        DateOfBirth1970-01-01
        MaritalStatusMaritalStatus.getTypeKey("S")
        LicenseNumber(generated, starts with B)
        LicenseStateJurisdiction.getTypeKey("CA")
        AutoSyncTC_SUSPENDED
        OfficialID999-99-code (if withDefaultOfficialID is true)
        TaxID999-99-code (if withDefaultOfficialID is true)
        PrimaryPhoneTypeTC_WORK
        EmailAddress1(generated, starting with code)
        EmailAddress2(generated, starting with code)
        VendorTypeautoglass
        FirstName(generated, ends with code)
        LastName(generated, ends with code)
        CellPhoneCountryTC_US
        CellPhone650-333-3333
        Parameters:
        code - this value (up to 4 digits) is incorporated as a prefix or suffix into many of the generated values, e.g. email, firs/last name, SSN
        withDefaultOfficialID - if true, then an SSN is generated and used in both OfficialID and TaxID
